title.narrative: 2.4 Water, Sanitation, and Hygiene (WASH) AND DISASTER RESPONSE

description.narrative: By the end of 2013 at least 80% of disaster-stricken people will have access to safe water, hygiene, sanitation and treatment of SAM for the under 5 years old and the vulnerable populations in the flood-prone areas will have access to water, sanitation and hygiene infrastructures, which contributes to Sanitation, Water. UNICEF aims to achieve this through Systems Strengthening And Institution Building. This contributes to the following Country Programme result: Programme Component Results (PCR) 2: By the end of 2013, 50% of infants (both boys and girls) are protected against the transmission of HIV from mother to child 95% of children under five (boys and girls) are protected against measles, polio and intestinal parasites, as well as Vitamin A and iodine deficiency 80% of children sleep under insecticide treated nets and 80% of children and women in emergency situations have access to an integrated package of preventive and curative services to reduce risks related to natural disasters and other emergencies.
